    <h1 class='post__title__title mv025 noe theme__text' >How ‘Event Scripts’ Structure Our Personal Memories</h1>
    <div class='post__title__author-date h5 mt1'>
            <div class='byline relative flex flex-items-start merriweather mv025 mr1 gray3 h6t theme__text-hover'>
        <em class='byline__by gray4 mr075'>By </em>
                    <a href='https://www.quantamagazine.org/authors/ingrid-wickelgren/'>
                <span class='byline__author uppercase kern light small'>Ingrid Wickelgren</span>
            </a>
            </div>
<p class="h6 mv1 pv025 o6"><em>February 21, 2025</em></p>    </div>
    <div class='post__title__meta flex flex-wrap flex-items-start'>
        <div class='post__title__excerpt wysiwyg p italic mb1 mt025 pr2 o4 theme__text ' >
            By screening films in a brain scanner, neuroscientists discovered a rich library of neural scripts — from a trip through an airport to a marriage proposal — that form scaffolds for memories of our experiences.        </div>
